Poor grammar.  The article "an" should be used instead of "a" when it comes before a word that starts with a vowel, (except for long U such as University), and "an" should also be used before silent h (heir, honor, hour,honest).  "An" is used when the next word pronounced phonetically starts with a vowel, (sounds like it starts with a vowel).  You can look up the phonetic spellings in dictionaries.  Phonetically, long U is spelled "ju".  The 'J' in phonics sounds like the 'y' in yellow.
